                type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On June 18, 1954, the forces of Lieutenant Colonel <persName corresp="#p_CAC1"
                        >Carlos Castillo Armas</persName>, a Guatemalan army officer in exile,
                    crossed the Guatemalan border from Honduras at three points in a movement aimed
                    at overthrowing the government of President <persName corresp="#p_AGJ1"
                        >Arbenz</persName>. Numerous telegrams and despatches from Guatemala
                    reporting the activities of <persName corresp="#p_CAC1">Castillo
                        Armas</persName>’ followers are in file 714.00. For information concerning
                    the reaction of the United States Government to the developments in Guatemala,
                    see the statement released by the Department of State, dated June 19, in the
                    Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, June 28, 1954, pages
                    981–982.</p>
            </div>
